  content: `Plan 0008 - Real-client Hybrid Delivery. Goal: deliver real client engagements to a quality bar suitable for the ICUMD launch portfolio, while extracting tooling-grade source material from each engagement via a non-negotiable harvest discipline - the two engagements jointly serve as real-world pipeline validation, replacing the synthetic TKT Trio test as the first round of tooling refinement. The core shape: multiple concurrent delivery threads (originally Ghost Media and Ben's Trees, later re-scoped to Public Service Center and Ben's Trees, plus ICUMD launch prep) all feeding a single harvest-pass-per-milestone mechanism into a central tooling backlog, which in turn feeds Track D. Status: the methodology has been operationally in force since roughly 2026-06-01 - the harvest passes, the central tooling-backlog, and the full internal-artefact-set discipline are all genuinely running, most visibly on Public Service Center (19 harvest passes logged as of the 2026-07-02 audit). The plan's own formal sign-off gate was never explicitly triggered, which was corrected at the 2026-07-02 re-sync (now marked "in execution, retro-acknowledged"). Scope was also corrected the same day - the plan is now understood as scoped around Public Service Center (the actual flagship engagement, engagement #1) and Ben's Trees (engagement #2, currently paused), with Ghost Media parked and TKT Trio remaining the third validation run. A known weakness the 2026-07-02 audit exposed: the harvest discipline works excellently at the per-repo level but the escalation step into the central outputs/tooling-backlog.md had no trigger and stalled for roughly 18 days - the fix for that specific gap is specified in the coordination-layer tooling plans (0011/0012).`
