  path: "plans/0011-coordination-layer-tooling.md",
  type: "status", tags: ["plan", "coordination", "audit", "tooling"], strategy: "digest",
  content: `Plan 0011 - Coordination-Layer Tooling: Repo Health, Drift Detection, Harvest Promotion. Goal: close three systemic gaps exposed by the 2026-07-02 full cross-cutting audit - uncommitted work sitting at loss-risk in multiple repos, the Command Center workspace drifting weeks behind actual repo reality, and the harvest-to-central-backlog promotion step silently stalling - with small tools rather than more discipline, per Plan 0008's own principle that if a discipline keeps getting skipped, the discipline (not the goal) is the thing to fix. Three tools proposed: (1) a /repo-health command that scans a machine-readable roster of repos and reports uncommitted/unpushed work ranked by age, which would have caught the ICUMD and Ben's Trees situations within a week instead of a month; (2) drift detection wired into session start (via this workspace's CLAUDE.md) that compares status.md's freshness against actual repo commit activity and warns before presenting a confident-but-stale picture; (3) a harvest-promotion trigger - a mechanical aggregator that surfaces unpromoted HARVEST.md candidates across repos, paired with a named promotion step added to the harvest-pass template itself, since promotion decisions stay deliberately human per the existing rule-of-three validation gates. Status: the proposal has an executable implementation plan (Plan 0012) ready to run.`
